    "title": "WFMY News 2 receives 5 Emmy nominations | wfmynews2.com",
    "text": "We are so proud of Team 2 for their commitment to telling stories important to you! Check out what we were nominated for and watch some stories for yourself! Daily News Report – Single Shift Total Eclipse of the Heart Reporter Ben Briscoe and Photographer Crosby Sensibaugh were nominated. Sportscast One Shining Moment in 2024? Sports Anchor Amanda Ferguson was nominated. News 2 was also nominated for these newscasts: Weekend Newscast “Protecting Until The End: The Murder of Sgt. Dale Nix” The following were nominated: - Kim Ballard, News Director - Alyson Olivo, Executive Producer - Benjamin Briscoe, Anchor - Micaela Curry, Director - Edward Orzech, Producer - Itinease McMiller, MSJ - Giselle Thomas, MSJ - Brian Hall, Photographer - Julian Morgan, Photographer Weathercast \"Hurricane Heads Up with Tim Buckley\" Chief Meteorologist Tim Buckley was nominated. As well as this sports story: Sports Story – News Feature (No production time limit) \"Fight Like Ophie\" Sports Anchor/ Reporter Amanda Ferguson was nominated. MORE WAYS TO GET WFMY NEWS 2 Subscribe to our daily newsletter [Let’s Get 2 It!](/email) Download the WFMY News 2 APP from your Apple or Google Play store. ADD THE WFMY+ APP TO YOUR FAVORITE STREAMING DEVICE ROKU: Add the channel from the ROKU store or by searching for WFMY. Amazon Fire TV: Search for WFMY to find the free app to add to your account. You can also add the app directly to your Fire TV through your Amazon account. Follow us: Facebook | https://bit.ly/3326pAY Twitter | https://bit.ly/2vIPZkT Instagram | https://bit.ly/39Ghs5a",
